{"sectionId":702,"sectionIdLiteral":"702","humanId":"lesson-284","volumeId":"workbook","locale":"en","titleInfo":{"title":"I can elect to change all thoughts that hurt.","ownlineNumber":"Lesson 284"},"annotation":"W-284","bodyHtml":"<div class=\"acim-text lesson-284\"> <div data-paragraph-id=\"702#1\"><p class=\"p-normal\"><span class=\"pnr\">1.</span> <span data-sentence-id=\"702#1:1\"><span class=\"snr noprint\">1</span>Loss is not loss when properly perceived.</span> <span data-sentence-id=\"702#1:2\"><span class=\"snr\">2</span>Pain is impossible.</span> <span data-sentence-id=\"702#1:3\"><span class=\"snr\">3</span>There is no grief with any cause at all.</span> <span data-sentence-id=\"702#1:4\"><span class=\"snr\">4</span>And suffering of any kind is nothing but a dream.</span> <span data-sentence-id=\"702#1:5\"><span class=\"snr\">5</span>This is the truth, at first to be but said and then repeated many times; and next to be accepted as but partly true, with many reservations.</span> <span data-sentence-id=\"702#1:6\"><span class=\"snr\">6</span>Then to be considered seriously more and more, and finally accepted as the truth.</span> <span data-sentence-id=\"702#1:7\"><span class=\"snr\">7</span>I can elect to change all thoughts that hurt.</span> <span data-sentence-id=\"702#1:8\"><span class=\"snr\">8</span>And I would go beyond these words today, and past all reservations, and arrive at full acceptance of the truth in them.</span></p></div> <div data-paragraph-id=\"702#2\"><p class=\"p-italic\"><span class=\"pnr\">2.</span> <span data-sentence-id=\"702#2:1\"><span class=\"snr noprint\">1</span>Father, what You have given cannot hurt, so grief and pain must be impossible.</span> <span data-sentence-id=\"702#2:2\"><span class=\"snr\">2</span>Let me not fail to trust in You today, accepting but the joyous as Your gifts; accepting but the joyous as the truth.</span></p></div> </div>","firstWords":"Loss is not loss when properly perceived. Pain is impossible. T